From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 20:15:00 +0800
Subject: Normalize GPU machine model info to prevent hardware fingerprinting

Overrides machine_model_name and machine_model_version in
FillGPUInfoFromSystemInfo() when PureCloak noise is enabled.
Both values are set to generic defaults ("Default" / "1.0") to
prevent hardware-identifying machine model strings from leaking
through the GPU info API.

---
 gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc b/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
--- a/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
+++ b/gpu/config/gpu_info_collector.cc
@@ -795,6 +795,15 @@ void FillGPUInfoFromSystemInfo(GPUInfo* gpu_info,
 
   gpu_info->machine_model_name = system_info->machineModelName;
   gpu_info->machine_model_version = system_info->machineModelVersion;
+
+#if BUILDFLAG(IS_PURECLOAK)
+  // PureCloak: normalize machine model info to prevent hardware fingerprinting.
+  // Use a consistent model name when noise is enabled.
+  if (purecloak::PureCloakSeed::GetInstance()->noise_enabled()) {
+    gpu_info->machine_model_name = "Default";
+    gpu_info->machine_model_version = "1.0";
+  }
+#endif
 }
 
 void CollectGraphicsInfoForTesting(GPUInfo* gpu_info) {
